e\n      \u003ctd style=\"background-color: #F5F5F5; border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e開講場所\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003eSFC\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"background-color: #F5F5F5; border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e授業形態\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e実習・演習\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"background-color: #F5F5F5; border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e履修者制限\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e\n      \u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"background-color: #F5F5F5; border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e履修条件\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e\n        \u003cp\u003eNONE\u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cp\u003eWe will use recent examples of geopolitical events and incidents (e.g. Covid 19 impact) to discuss some of the most important aspects of modern (cyber) society. Students are encouraged to follow activities of the Cyber Civilization Research Center.\u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n      \u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"background-color: #F5F5F5; border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e使用言語\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e英語\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"background-color: #F5F5F5; border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e連絡先\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003ecmaracke@sfc.keio.ac.jp\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"background-color: #F5F5F5; border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e授業ホームページ\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"background-color: #F5F5F5; border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e同一科目\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e\n        \u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n      \u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"background-color: #F5F5F5; border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e学生が利用する予定機材/ソフト等\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e\n        \u003cp\u003eNo special software required, however, as the class will be conducted online, access to Internet and video conferencing system is required\u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n      \u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"background-color: #F5F5F5; border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e設置学部・研究科\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e総合政策・環境情報学部\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"background-color: #F5F5F5; border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e大学院プロジェクト名\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"background-color: #F5F5F5; border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e大学院プロジェクトサブメンバー\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e\n        \u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n      \u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"background-color: #F5F5F5; border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003eゲストスピーカーの人数\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e0\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"background-color: #F5F5F5; border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e履修選抜・課題タイプ=テキスト登録可\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003efalse\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"background-color: #F5F5F5; border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e履修選抜・選抜課題タイプ=ファイル登録可\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003efalse\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"background-color: #F5F5F5; border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003eGIGAサティフィケート対象\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003etrue\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"background-color: #F5F5F5; border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e最終更新日\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e2020/08/11 14:17:49\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n  \u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\u003ch3 style=\"background-color: #394B58; color: white; padding-left: 8px; font-weight: bold;\"\u003e科目概要\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe objective of this course is to give students an introduction to critical legal thinking by studying the nature of “law” and providing an overview of “legal reasoning”. The topics will address many different issues and debates but we will focus particularly on the following questions:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWhat is the role of law in our society? \u003cbr\u003eHow does law justify itself? \u003cbr\u003eHow does law relate to ethics and morality? \u003cbr\u003eWhat happens when opposing rights conflict with each other? \u003cbr\u003eWhat defines power in a juridical system? \u003cbr\u003eWhat are the strength and weaknesses of democracy?\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 style=\"background-color: #394B58; color: white; padding-left: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; font-weight: bold;\"\u003e授業シラバス\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"background-color: #ccecff; padding-left: 8px; margin-top: 0; font-weight: bold;\"\u003e主題と目標／授業の手法など\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe goal of this class is to develop logical and legal thinking skills while expanding a deeper understanding of the many faces of law and its role in society. Because of the nature of this class and the way it is conducted, students are expected to participate actively in the discussions and contribute to the debate through students’ presentations. The class will be held in English and give students an additional opportunity to work, argue and present in English.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4 style=\"background-color: #ccecff; padding-left: 8px; font-weight: bold;\"\u003e教材・参考文献\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNONE\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4 style=\"background-color: #ccecff; padding-left: 8px; font-weight: bold;\"\u003e提出課題・試験・成績評価の方法など\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e50% presentations and assignments 50% participation and attendance\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4 style=\"background-color: #ccecff; padding-left: 8px; font-weight: bold;\"\u003e履修上の注意\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNo restrictions - all students welcome!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003ch4 style=\"background-color: #ccecff; padding-left: 8px; font-weight: bold;\"\u003e授業計画\u003c/h4\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第1回 Orientation and Introduction\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe first session will give an overview of the course, and give students an opportunity to introduce themselves, explain why they are taking the course and what their interests are:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e- Overview of the class and the following weeks\u003cbr\u003e- Discuss the following questions: What is law? What is “legal thinking”?\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第2回 Legal Thinking\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e- Thinking and discussing about norms and values, culture and society\u003cbr\u003e- History of law\u003cbr\u003e- Morals, ethics and law: Basic philosophy and basic jurisprudence\u003cbr\u003e- Different schools of thought in general jurisprudence (e.g. “natural law”, “legal positivism”)\u003cbr\u003e- Connection between law and morality?\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第3回 Law and Justice\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eDifferent schools of thought in general jurisprudence (e.g. “natural law”, “legal positivism”)\u003cbr\u003e- Connection between law and morality - Details and examples\u003cbr\u003e- Law and legal thinking in in everyday life\u003cbr\u003e- Examples and court cases\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第4回 Law and Power\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e- What is power?\u003cbr\u003e- Introduction to constitutional law\u003cbr\u003e- How are laws changed? Why do they need to be changed over time?\u003cbr\u003e- Critical thinking about law and power\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第5回 Student Presentation I\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e- Overview: Structure of the presentations (arguments and defense arguments)\u003cbr\u003e- Topic finding\u003cbr\u003e- Discussion and scheduling for the coming weeks\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第6回 Student Presentation II\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e- Topics to be discussed\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第7回 Student Presentation III\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e- Topics to be discussed\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第8回 Student Presentation IV\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e- Topics to be discussed\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第9回 Student Presentation V\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e- Topics to be discussed\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第10回 Human Rights and Freedom of Speech\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e- Overview of human rights / examples\u003cbr\u003e- Freedom of speech and social impact\u003cbr\u003e- Hate speech, false information and freedom of speech\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第11回 Law, Society and Technology\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e- How does law control society and how does society control law?\u003cbr\u003e- Law and legal consciousness in everyday life?\u003cbr\u003e- Law and technology - “Digital locks” (discussing Ian Kerr)\u003cbr\u003e- The concept of responsibility in the digital age (revisiting Hans Jonas)\u003cbr\u003e- New laws for new technologies?\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第12回 Future of Law\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e- What changes should/could be made in the light of new technologies?\u003cbr\u003e- What changes should/could be made in the light of the global information society?\u003cbr\u003e- Law and globalization\u003cbr\u003e- Concept of responsibility\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第13回 Leadership Case Study\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e- What is leadership?\u003cbr\u003e- Why is leadership important in today's (cyber) society?\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第14回 Ethics Case Study\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e- What is ethics?\u003cbr\u003e- How do we define ethical leadership and decision making in today's (cyber) society?\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第15回 Summary, Wrap Up and Open Questions\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e- What have we learned?\u003cbr\u003e- What comes next?\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n\n  \u003cu\u003e15回目に相当するその他の授業計画\u003c/u\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n","course_code":"リーガルワークショップ","default_view":"modules","root_account_id":1,"enrollment_term_id":3,"license":null,"grade_passback_setting":null,"end_at":null,"public_s